## security/ — Identity & Authentication

- [x] Persistent node identity (ZDXNodeIdentity, disk-backed, survives restart)
- [x] Node identity consistency — ZDXNode, ZDXNodeAgent, detect_capabilities()
      all use ZDXNodeIdentity as single source of truth (no independent uuid4() calls)
- [x] Ed25519 keypair generation + persistent storage
- [x] Private key permission hardening (0600)
- [x] node_id deterministically derived from public key hash
- [x] Signed protocol envelope (version, timestamp, nonce, sequence, node_id, payload, signature)
- [x] Signature verification layer
- [ ] key_store.py — OS-specific secure storage, encrypted export/recovery, rotation support
- [ ] session_auth.py — HELLO handshake, challenge/response, authenticated sessions
- [ ] replay_guard.py — nonce tracking, sequence validation, stale message rejection
- [ ] revocation.py — revoked identity registry
- [ ] Revocation checked per-session or per-message (not just at initial handshake)

## Networking / Transport

- [x] Length-prefixed JSON envelope protocol (zdx_network.py)
- [x] Message size limits enforced (send + receive)
- [x] TCP server accepting connections, routing by message kind (zdx_server.py)
- [ ] Server returns real enrollment status (pending/approved/unknown) on
      identity/capability messages — currently acks unconditionally
- [ ] try/except around message decode — malformed peer input shouldn't
      crash a handler thread
- [ ] Socket timeout on accepted connections (currently blocks indefinitely
      on a silent peer)
- [ ] Peers keyed by node_id, not socket address (depends on identity
      consistency fix being live in zdx_server.py)
- [ ] TLS / encrypted transport (currently plaintext TCP — documented future work)

